CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 4, 1958, pg. A14, reads: "Golden-Age Party - Some of the members of the Home Department of Warren Methodist Church School enjoyed a Golden-Age party on their 33rd anniversary.  Held in the dining room of the church, the following were entertained lavishly.  Clockwise about the table are Mmes. Virginia Greer, Geraldine Bradford, Addie E. Gupton, superintendent of the group for the entire 33 years; Ethel Jones, Mary Williams, Anne Cypress, Anna M. Green, Essie Carter and Luchal Taylor.  A fine crowd attended. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women and men, including members of Home Department of Warren Methodist Church, Virginia Greer, Geraldine Bradford, Addie E. Gupton, Ethel Jones, Mary Williams, Anne Cypress, Anna M. Green, Essie Carter and Luchal Taylor, gathered around table for 33rd anniversary party
